Package org.apache.juneau.annotation

General bean annotations

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Null
    Represents a null entry in a class annotation.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Bean
    Used to tailor how beans get interpreted by the framework.
    BeanConstructor
    Maps constructor arguments to property names on beans with read-only properties.
    BeanIgnore
    Ignore classes, fields, and methods from being interpreted as bean or bean components.
    BeanProperty
    Used tailor how bean properties get interpreted by the framework.
    Consumes
    Annotation used on subclasses of Parser to identify the media types that it consumes.
    NameProperty
    Identifies a setter as a method for setting the name of a POJO as it's known by its parent object.
    Overrideable
    Identifies a method as specifically designed to be overridden and augmented.
    ParentProperty
    Identifies a setter as a method for adding a parent reference to a child object.
    Pojo
    Used to tailor how POJOs get interpreted by the framework.
    Produces
    Annotation used on subclasses of Serializer to identify the media types that it produces.
    Remoteable
    Identifies services whose Java class or methods can be invoked remotely.
    ThreadSafe
    Identifies a class as being thread-safe.
    URI
    Used to identify a class or bean property as a URI.
